raw_data.description: A slow moving Monday morning. A fast paced Wednesday lunch break. An easy and pleasant Saturday afternoon. No matter where you are in your week (or your day), you can count on Salted Melon to have exactly what you need, sometimes before you know you need it.

reviews_data.review_text: Healthy options! Fresh & great value.
Nice place,  with excellent food and coffee.
Outstanding food and widely accommodating menu. Super clean, practical, and expedient counter service

I had been seeing the Salted Melon whenever we would search for food and i finally gave them a try. I thought the layout of the restaurant was very unique and felt it was a great place for someone to go eat while getting some work done. I ordered the Globe Trotter Wrap with the Truffle Fries and Hibiscus Tea!!! The Truffle Fries stole my heart almost instantly 10/10 Easily! The wrap was good and gave "Clean Eating" vibes, 9/10 because I felt it could use something to give it a little umph! Maybe next time I will try a sauce to go on it which just may do it for me. All in all its a great place to go try out if you haven't already. ❤️

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Outdoor patio / terrace

reviews_data.review_text: Haley from Salted Melon went above and beyond in her customer service. Our team had a wonderful lunch two days in a row from this restaurant and we want to say a big thank you to Haley who helped us with the ordering and delivery. She always followed through and responded to phone calls and emails and was so kind. Thank you, Haley!

Salted melon was a real.surprise! Super laid back...food was very good! Lots of fresh vegterbles/ pistachios/ dried cherries/ shredded Brussels sprouts....and add in that homemade in house dressing~~~just spectacular! The atmosphere was comfortable and comfy...no frills...just good tasty food!!!
Go try it!
You'll see for yourself...
Love this concept but boy was the chicken super dry. Couldn’t eat our bowl or wrap

This is an adorable place to eat.  it was our first time eating at any of their locations.  This location
is counter service only.  They take your order and give you a number and bring you your food.  The challenge was to find seating, as it was so crowded.  They do have tables outside as well.   The food was delish!  It’s a little pricey as 1 sandwich with pasta salad, 1 chicken salad plate and one Ice tea with tip was $48.00.  Also, it’s a smaller place and it was incredibly loud, so if you’re looking to have a deep conversation sitting outside might be best.   We’ll definately be back.

Our first time at Salted Melon was fantastic! The food was absolutely delicious and healthy fresh, the atmosphere was warm and welcoming, and we all left full and happy. A special thanks to Chandler, the manager, who made us feel right at home — her kindness and energy truly stood out. We’re already excited to come back! Perfect spot for a good family meal.
Such a cute place to sit outside and relax! The food was great and Grace went above and beyond to accommodate our group!

I got the salmon bowl and a side of pesto couscous. This place was so cute. I love the color palette and the staff. I felt very welcomed and they answered all my questions without exasperation which was very different than what I expected from a “casual” place. My only complaint is that the music is too loud. I’ll be coming back for sure. I loved how colorful the food was and how balanced it was
Excellent customer service.  Delicious food.
Very good service. The smoothie I ordered came out efficiently and it was delicious! Thank you to Adelyn, who took my order and made my experience enjoyable!

Me and my friends came here at June 26 around 3:30ish. The food was immaculate and so fresh and healthy. The amount you get is a good amount for the price. I am writing this specifically because Chandler did such an amazing job with customer service and came back and checked on us. She is truly a great person to have around at this place. All restaurants can taste good but the service here is 10/10. The others were great as well. You've got a good crew here.

It’s really good! I loved my salmon wrap. The employees are great. And I love the design of this place! More restaurants should take notes. Great new location in Phillips Place!! Really easy parking and they have 2 patios!

What a breath of fresh air in SouthPark!!

On behalf of the Hampton Inn and Suites at Phillips Place; we are so delighted to welcome our new neighbor to the shopping center. Hannah and Thomas were so amazing and sent us some catering options to our staff to sample and we were blown away. From their breakfast burritos to their steak sandwiches and buffalo bowls we couldn't stop raving about the tenderness of the meats and flavor packed into every dish. Their presentation for catering was bright, exciting and well put together. Their catering options left us craving more; we picked up lunch their opening week and were greeted with polite and fast service along with bright decor and even better vibes.

This is the perfect stop for in-between zoom calls or a refreshing lunch outing with the family this summer. So excited to keep sampling their menu and promote to all of our guests.

reviews_data.review_text: Such a great spot — cozy vibes, tasty coffee, and super friendly staff!
I'm so glad Salted Melon opened up a location near SouthPark. The coffee options are great. Food menu is good too.
Great coffee and food. The vibes and the staff are great.
